<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 4:10AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow tonight above 7000 feet...
An area of snow is expected to affect the northern half of
Beaverhead County tonight. Snow levels could fall to around 7000
feet this evening. Thus Big Hole and Chief Joseph passes could be
affected.
Snow accumulations of 3 to 6 inches are possible above 7000 feet
by Monday morning. Thus anyone recreating at higher elevations
tonight should be prepared for winter like conditions.</description>
